<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,1458,1726]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,652,1458,1484]" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732">
Gaster 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[248,652,1458,1484]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732">
(
<figureCitation box="[256,378,1458,1484]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1478,1501]" captionTargetBox="[169,1148,147,1445]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[163,1153,142,1446]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 16. Bembix arabica Edmardash &amp; Gadallah, sp.nov. (male holotype): (a) Dorsal habitus; (b) Frontal view of head; (c) Frontal view of head (showing labrum); (d) Lateral view of head, thorax and basal part of gaster." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5530076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5530076/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732">Figures 16</figureCitation>
(a), 17(c) and 18(a–c)).
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Terga densely, very finely punctate; T7 not incised laterally, broadly rounded apically, T 
<quantity box="[648,688,1493,1518]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
form of two, finger-like narrow processes. Sterna shiny, S2 with longitudinal carina medially (with no keel), sparsely punctate posteriorly, with dense punctures at base; remaining of sterna sparsely punctate laterally, S6 with pointed elevation medio-posteriorly; S7 with longitudinal carina medially; S8 with postero-median, relatively long and sharply pointed prolongation. Genitalia with parameres bulged preapically, and slightly notched at apex, penis valve slightly shorter than gonocoxite (
<figureCitation box="[301,408,1701,1726]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="35.[160,225,1329,1352]" captionTargetBox="[171,1152,147,1296]" captionTargetId="figure-98@35.[163,1153,142,1297]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Figure 18. Bembix arabica Edmardash &amp; Gadallah, sp.nov. (male holotype): (a) Last gastral terga including genitalia; (b) Last gastral sterna including genitalia; (c) Last gastral sterna including genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5530084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5530084/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="1732">Figure 18</figureCitation>
(a–c)).
</paragraph>
